{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778260877,"nonce":"yZ7YRoNhfyd1he4dXqWtm0Curdw=","title":"Decoupling decomposition analysis: variance partition u_ff + K_local·error + residual","message":"Stage 8 in the proposed regulator-coupling / decoupling-chain programme (exploration, not committed). Analysis stage; depends on trained controllers from stages 4, 6, 7. Shares linearisation infrastructure with fixed-point analyses c044a24 and 17137e6.\n\n**Question.** Does the trained RNN actually decouple its policy into a feedforward drive and local error feedback, in the sense Gemini hypothesised? This directly tests whether the −25% Δv reflects a deliberate tracker-like policy rather than an evaluation artefact or training failure.\n\n**Method.**\n1. Compute a nominal trajectory x_nom(t) by averaging over many adversary samples.\n2. Fit a time-varying linearisation of the RNN's policy around x_nom(t): u_RNN(x,t) ≈ u_ff(t) + K_local(t)·(x − x_nom(t)) + higher_order(x, t, h_t).\n3. Measure the variance partition: how much of var(u) lives in u_ff, in K_local·error, and in the residual?\n4. Project K_local(t) onto the analytical Riccati K_*(t) and measure subspace overlap.\n\n**Analytical prediction.** Gemini's hypothesis: ||u_ff||_∞ large relative to ||K_local · x_nom||_∞ for the GRU; small for the linear regulator. Codex's \"underdetermined\" position: no clean separation.\n\n**Falsification.** If variance partition ≈ 100% in K_local·error and ≈ 0% in u_ff across all trained networks, GRU is behaving as a regulator — Gemini's mechanism is empirically absent. If mostly u_ff, Gemini is right.\n\n**Infrastructure overlap.** The K_local(t) linearisation uses the same Jacobian-of-policy infrastructure as fixed-point analyses c044a24 (fixed points during reaching) and 17137e6 (Jacobian eigendecomposition). Coordinate implementation.\n\n**Cross-refs.** Plan §3 stage 8. Analyses coord 4d38c15. Fixed-points issue c044a24. Jacobian-eig issue 17137e6.","files":null}]}